Subject: [PATCH] feat(context): hot/warm/cold memory tier enforcement
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

ao_kernel/context/memory_tiers.py:
- classify_tier(): confidence + age → hot/warm/cold
- enforce_tier_budgets(): cap each tier, overflow demotes to next
- load_tier_policy(): from bundled policy_context_memory_tiers.v1.json

Tiers:
- HOT: confidence >= 0.7 AND age < 7 days (max 30)
- WARM: confidence >= 0.4 OR age < 30 days (max 50)
- COLD: everything else (max 100)

10 new tests, 406 total passing.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
